I combed through the hair with the Denman.

00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:58.500
I pulled the hair very taut to make sure that the hair is stretched out.

00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:03.500
Some hairs in the back didn't get cut.

00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:07.500
And I snipped away those dead ends.

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:15.500
I used the "Curling Gel Souffle" by Shea Moisture to twist my hair again.

00:01:18.200 --> 00:01:20.500
And I twisted

00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:35.500
And twisted...

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:42.500
And twisted.

00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:48.500
Until I finally finished. hahaha

00:01:50.500 --> 00:01:53.000
I clipped the twist to help me know which twist I have already trimmed

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:54.000
I then repeated the same process for each twist!

00:02:03.500 --> 00:02:07.000
Step one: take the twist out

00:02:08.500 --> 00:02:12.000
Step two: Comb through the hair

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:30.000
Step three: pull the hair taut

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:40.000
Trim!

00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:47.000
Apply Gel

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
Then twist SUPER fast. hahaha

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:55.000
Then clip the twist

00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:47.000
For my layers/ bangs in the front...

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:56.000
I separated the pieces of hair based off of their length.

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:03.000
This makes sure that I am not trimming the longer pieces too short

